{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Requirements:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This REAPER script requires:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab REAPER 7.20+ (could work with older versions but has not been tested)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ReaPack\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab SWS/S&M REAPER extension\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab ReaImGUI\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Basic Installation:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Install script through ReaPack.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Repository Link: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/danielrdehaan/Random-Containers-for-Reaper/raw/master/index.xml"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
https://github.com/danielrdehaan/Random-Containers-for-Reaper/raw/master/index.xml
}}}
\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Full Installation Instructions:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://youtu.be/GTxrmEj5frs?si=mKpRhymZN-J_Dc-s"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
{\pict\jpegblip\picw480\pich360\picwgoal9600\pichgoal7200 }
}}}
\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Download and install ReaPack from {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://reapack.com"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
https://reapack.com
}}}
.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Restart REAPER after installing ReaPack.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Note: Users of macOS Catalina or newer may need to click on "Allow Anyway" in System Preferences > Security & Privacy after launching REAPER once for ReaPack to load when installed for the first time. Restart REAPER after approving.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Open ReaPack from the menu bar Extensions > ReaPack > Browse Packages... and install the following extensions:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab SWS/S&M extensions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab ReaImGui: ReaScript binding for Dear ImGui\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Restart Reaper\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Import a new repository via ReaPack by choose from the menu bar Extensions > ReaPack > Import Repositories...\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab Paste the following repository link in the resulting pop-up window and click "OK" https://github.com/danielrdehaan/Random-Containers-for-Reaper/raw/master/index.xml\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 7.\tx360\tab Browse for the newly imported repository via ReaPack by choosing from the menu bar Extensions > ReaPack > Browse Packages...\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 8.\tx360\tab Search for and install the "Random Containers for Reaper" package by "Simple Sound Tools"\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Running Random Containers for Reaper\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Open REAPER's Action List and search for the action "Script: Simple-Sound-Tools_Random-Containers.lua"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Assign a keyboard shortcut if desired.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Using Random Container for Reaper\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 The Window\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Random Container's window can be floated or docked to Reaper's docker. To dock the window simply drag it via it's menu bar to any of the sides of the main Reaper window.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Enabling Randomization During Playback\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The button located at the top of the Random Container window allows you to enable/disable the randomization of audio items during playback.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Randomizing Audio Item Parameters\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To randomize the parameters of an audio item simply select one or multiple audio items and...\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Enable the type of randomization you want to apply. Then...\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Adjust the amount and/or type of randomization you want for each parameter.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Advanced Options\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In some situation you may find that the script performs better if you set Reaper's Media Buffer Size to smaller values. This setting can be found in Reaper's Preferences > Buffering.\par}
}
